1. Download the zip folder and open the index.html file in your favourite browser.

2. The neighbourhood map application opens. You can choose from any of the locations displayed in the map by clicking the marker  	 in the map.

3. On clicking the marker, a small window opens displaying the information on the location from the foursquare website.

4. A small button on the top left corner is available which when clicked opens a menu with the list of locations marked in the 	 	map.

5. You can search the place you want in the search box. If the place is available, you will see the marker for that location in  	the map.

6. On clicking the place in the list view, the corresponding marker bounces to notify the location and also opening the 		 	infowindow.  